Two days have been set aside for legislators to either critique or applaud President Cyril Ramaphosa’s 2019 State of the Nation Address, with the first citizen expected to deliver his response on Thursday. ANC Chief Whip Jackson Mthembu will open the debate on Tuesday. During the debate, opposition political parties will put forward MPs to interrogate the state of the nation address. While ANC MPs will undoubtedly be deployed to praise Ramaphosa and the ANC’s tenure in government. Watch the live feed here: 